<BYLINE>By MARY R. SANDOK</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ST. PAUL, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The battle over abortion will involve young people today as the <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION> War did in the 1960s, former <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Rep. <PERSON> Bella </PERSON> <PERSON> Abzug </PERSON> told female political activists today. `` Abortion is the <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION> of this nation for young people everywhere,'' <PERSON> Abzug </PERSON> told the opening session of the National Women's Political Caucus' Biennial Convention. <PERSON> Abzug </PERSON>, a former <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> representative from <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> and a founder of the caucus 18 years ago, was the first of several speakers who are expected to address the abortion issue. The caucus runs through Sunday. `` No civilized nation can be allowed to declare an unborn fetus a person under the Constitution before women are declared persons under the Constitution,'' <PERSON> Abzug </PERSON> said. On Thursday, <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Ron </PERSON> <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> told the steering committee that the <ORGANIZATION> Democrats </ORGANIZATION> lost a chance to win the 1988 presidential election by not doing more to garner votes from women. `` In fact, we blew a major gender gap that might have carried the <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> candidate for president to the <ORGANIZATION> White </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION>,'' <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> said he understands `` the frustrations of working in the coalition.'' But he said those who counsel the formation of a third party `` ignore the second half of the adage that begins, ` United we stand.' `` No matter where the struggle for justice ... divided we will indeed fall and fail to reach our goals,'' he said. `` I have worked in the struggle for civil rights my entire adult life, and I do not d