 an important link between <LOCATION> Lima </LOCATION> and the rich farming and mining areas of the sierra. The Shining Path frequently targets the line as part of its strategy to cut the capital off from the rest of <LOCATION> Peru </LOCATION>. Two weeks ago the rebels dynamited the tracks under a train carrying copper ore, derailing all 18 cars. The Shining Path began its insurgency near <LOCATION> Ayacucho </LOCATION>, 235 miles southeast of <LOCATION> Lima </LOCATION>. The violence has spread through most of the Andean highlands, parts of the <LOCATION> Pacific </LOCATION> coastline and into the coca-producing jungles of the northeast.
