<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> dollar gained against <LOCATION> European </LOCATION> currencies this morning. Gold prices retreated from Thursday's peaks in <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> trading. Dealers attributed the dollar's advance during <LOCATION> Asian </LOCATION> and early European trading mostly to position-squaring ahead of the release today of July <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> unemployment figures. The threat of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> military action in the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> is lending additional support to the currency, they said. `` People had been already short, and then came the events in the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION>,'' said <PERSON> Manfred </PERSON> <PERSON> Totzauer </PERSON>, a dealer at <ORGANIZATION> Citibank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> AG </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Frankfurt </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>. `` The dollar is politically supported, and the -LRB- job -RRB- figures are already expected to be very weak, so the chances for a rise a good.'' In <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION>, the dollar closed at 138.05 yen, up 1.65 yen from Thursday. Later in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, the dollar declined to 137.85 yen. The pound traded at $ 1.6350, down from $ 1.6475 late Thursday. Other late dollar rates in <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>, compared with late Thursday: 1.8763 West German marks, up from 1.8650; 1.6147 Swiss francs, up from 1.6065; 6.3550 French francs, up from 6.3192; 2.1157 Dutch guilders, up from 2.0950; 1,351.80 Italian lire, up from 1,338.00, and 1.1740 Canadian dollars, up from 1.1715. Gold opened in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> at $ 371.90 a troy ounce, up from $ 369.75 late Thursday. At midmorning, the city's five major bullion dealers fixed a recommended price of $ 371.55 an ounce. In <LOCATION> Zurich </LOCATION>, gold traded at $ 371.50 an ounce. On Thursday, gold for August delivery closed at $ 373.70 a troy ounce on the Commodity Exchange in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. In <LOCATION> Hong </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kong </LOCATION> today, gold closed at $ 372.86 an ounce, up $ 2.19 from Thursday's figure. Silver was trading in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> at $ 5.29 a troy ounce, up from $ 5.23 an ounce late Thursday.
